title: VP of Engineering
bio: Former Google engineer who built TechVault's real-time data platform from scratch. Known for strong opinions on monorepo architecture.
notes: Key decision maker. Very direct communicator. Prefers data-driven pitches.

title: Founder & CEO
bio: Serial entrepreneur on his third startup. NeuralPulse just closed a $12M Series A for AI-powered diagnostics.
notes: Extremely charismatic. Tends to dominate conversations. High-value connector.

title: Chief Data Scientist
bio: Published 15 papers on transformer architectures. Previously led ML at Stripe. DataWeave does real-time market intelligence.
notes: Brilliant but introverted. Needs warm introductions. Technical depth is extraordinary.

title: CTO
bio: Built the deployment platform that 2000+ startups use. Obsessed with developer ergonomics.
notes: Quiet until you ask about infrastructure. Then unstoppable. Strong technical credibility.

title: Head of Product
bio: Transformed Luminos from a clinic tool to a platform serving 500 hospitals. Background in nursing informatics.
notes: Extremely empathetic. Excellent at finding unexpected connections between people. High EQ.

title: Head of Engineering
bio: Built CryptoVault's ZK-proof identity verification system. Previously security researcher at Trail of Bits.
notes: Niche expertise. May not align with event theme but brings unique perspective on privacy tech.

title: Co-founder
bio: Synthetiq generates photorealistic product images for e-commerce. 40M images generated. Ex-Adobe researcher.
notes: Very creative thinker. Excellent at demos. Tends to go on tangents. Visual learner.

title: VP Sales
bio: Took ScaleStack from $2M to $45M ARR in 3 years. Known as a kingmaker in the NYC enterprise scene.
notes: Master networker. Knows everyone. Very transactional but delivers on promises.

title: Director of AI Programs
bio: Built MindShift's AI tutoring platform used by 200K students. PhD in Computational Linguistics from MIT.
notes: Deep thinker. Asks the uncomfortable questions about AI ethics. Respected voice in EdTech circles.

title: General Partner
bio: Manages $200M fund focused on AI infrastructure. Led investments in 3 unicorns. Former Goldman Sachs.
notes: Power player. Everyone wants his attention. Very selective about time allocation.

title: ML Engineer
bio: Core contributor to three major open-source vision models. AutoScribe does document understanding. Rising star.
notes: Junior but exceptional talent. No event history with us. Strong GitHub presence (12K followers).

title: CEO
bio: GreenLoop tracks supply chain carbon for Fortune 500 companies. $8M revenue. B-Corp certified.
notes: Passionate about intersection of AI and sustainability. Excellent storyteller. Very genuine.

title: Design Director
bio: Built design systems for Spotify and Airbnb before founding PixelCraft. Known for accessible-first design philosophy.
notes: Quietly influential. Her Twitter threads on AI+design go viral regularly. Values authenticity.

title: Founder
bio: BeatStack uses AI to help producers collaborate remotely in real-time. 50K active users. Ex-Spotify audio engineer.
notes: High energy. Life of the party. Might not be directly relevant but could spark creative cross-pollination.

title: CISO
bio: Former NSA turned startup CISO. SecureMind does AI-powered threat detection. 300 enterprise clients.
notes: No-nonsense. Skeptical of hype. But when she endorses something her network listens. Very trustworthy.

title: Senior Engineer
bio: Built Nullify's WASM-based code analysis tool. 23 years old. Won three hackathons this year.
notes: Very young and green socially but genuine prodigy. Could be a wildcard addition for pure technical energy.

title: VP of Research
bio: Led the team that created Artisan's self-improving manufacturing AI. 40+ cited papers. Ex-DeepMind.
notes: World-class researcher. Somewhat aloof but deeply generous with knowledge when engaged.

title: COO
bio: Scaled QuickShip's AI routing from 100 to 10K deliveries/day. MBA from Wharton. Very operations-minded.
notes: Practical thinker. Cuts through BS fast. Great at implementation but less interested in pure research.

title: Executive Director
bio: Runs BridgeAI which connects AI companies with underserved communities. Advisor to the White House on AI equity.
eventHistory: AI Summit 2024;Aspen Ideas Festival;UN AI Summit
notes: Tremendous moral authority. Her presence elevates any event. Zero revenue alignment but massive prestige value.

title: Data Engineer
bio: Solid data engineer who maintains a popular dbt package. Nice guy. Not a thought leader.
notes: Fills a seat but doesn't move needles. Low connection. Consider only if capacity allows.

title: Chief Science Officer
bio: Led three drug discovery programs using AI. Novex Bio has two compounds in Phase II trials. Rockstar in biotech-AI.
notes: Highest potential deal value. Very busy. Needs white-glove treatment. Her presence alone attracts other biotech leaders.

title: Head of AI
bio: RouteIQ's AI saves logistics companies 23% on fuel costs. Previously at Uber's autonomous vehicle division.
notes: Quietly competent. More interested in problems than networking. Needs introduction to the right people.

title: Product Lead
bio: VoxPop's AI companion app has 2M MAU. 26 years old. Gen Z product intuition that older founders lack.
notes: Energetic and creative. Might bring fresh perspective. Not well-connected in our network yet.

title: Managing Director
bio: Runs a $50M AI consulting practice. Knows every CTO in the Fortune 500. Old-school but adapting.
notes: Walking Rolodex. Not technical but opens doors. Some find him schmoozy. Undeniable network power.

title: Research Fellow
skills: fairness in ML;audit frameworks;policy analysis;technical writing
bio: Published the most-cited AI audit framework of 2024. Advises EU on AI Act implementation. Very principled.
notes: No revenue potential. But her ethical perspective prevents groupthink. Important voice to have in the room.
